ITEM 5 400 ADJ1=468
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 1
The daily water nymph show has been postponed due to lack of nymphs. Courtesy of the Fayd Chamber of Commerce.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The fountain is quite a marvel: made of smooth blue marble streaked with white, it continuously sprays streaming water, sparkling with golden light. There is a painted sign on the fountain.
*DESCRIPTION_END
PUT 0 198 VAL2=100 VAL3=0
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 4
The proud form of a beloved King stands guard over the city he loved.
The brilliance of the statue portrays King Frederick Kentaurus the III
at the height of his power. His chiseled body is covered in a suit of
golden plate armor, with the symbol of the Kentaraus family emblazoned
across the breast plate. Strong hands easily grip the pommel of the
beautiful alyzorn weapon crafted for kings and the compassionate black
eyes seem to gaze out across the entire city, ever on guard for any
signs of trouble. A golden plaque has been imbedded at the bottom of
the statue.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 5
Highly stylized lettering flows across the face of the plaque.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 5
              KING FREDERICK KENTAURUS THE III

            "I hear his name and see his face..."

         "Caught upon the wings of the morning breeze,"
           "Carried on strands of golden sunlight,"
        "Reflected in the waters of the clear blue seas,"
       "Painted by the glittering stars in the dark night."

         "Never to be forgotten, never to be diminished."
                "Always near in heart and mind"
        "Echoing forever, down the endless halls of time."
*DESCRIPTION_END
