This granite house standing on the east side of the street resembles a small castle. Iron bars extend over each of the windows, and a portcullis stands guard over a huge oak door with heavy steel bands. Above the door hangs a coat of arms depicting a flame-breathing black dragon. A pennant with the crest of the Crimson Band flutters in the breeze from the spire at the top of the building. Several hacked and splintered practice-dummies used for the honing of sword-fighting techniques are in the yard.
